<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,1580,1746]" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">
This new species most resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Y. H. Tan, S. S. Zhou &amp; B. Yang" authorityName="Y. H. Tan, S. S. Zhou &amp; B. Yang" authorityYear="2018" box="[457,881,1652,1674]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Trivalvaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="casseabriae">
<emphasis box="[457,595,1652,1673]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">T. casseabriae</emphasis>
Y.H.Tan, S.S.Zhou &amp; B.Yang
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Yang, B. &amp; Zhou, S. S. &amp; Ding, H. B. &amp; Li, R. &amp; Maung, K. W. &amp; Tan, Y. H." box="[909,1105,1652,1674]" pageId="1" pageNumber="80" pagination="3 - 12" refId="ref5836" refString="Yang, B., Zhou, S. S., Ding, H. B., Li, R., Maung, K. W. &amp; Tan, Y. H. (2018) Two new species of Trivalvaria (Annonaceae) from northern Myanmar. PhytoKeys 94: 3 - 12. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / phytokeys. 94.21553" type="journal article" year="2018">
Yang 
<emphasis box="[964,1012,1652,1673]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">et al.</emphasis>
(2018: 5)
</bibRefCitation>
in its small flowers with short white petals, but the petals are only ca. 
<quantity box="[506,560,1688,1709]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="80" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
long and strongly recurved versus 
<quantity box="[895,986,1688,1710]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="80" unit="mm" value="8.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="6.0">6–10 mm</quantity>
long and spreading, and the leaves are elliptic to oblanceolate with a maximum width of 
<quantity box="[572,637,1724,1746]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.8" pageId="1" pageNumber="80" unit="cm" value="6.8">6.8 cm</quantity>
versus lanceolate to oblong with a maximum width of 
<quantity box="[1167,1232,1724,1746]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="80" unit="cm" value="5.5">5.5 cm</quantity>
(
<tableCitation box="[1244,1316,1724,1746]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="3.[136,224,735,759]" captionText="TABLE 1. A morphological comparison of the three new Trivalvaria species (names in bold) to the most similar congener of each. Data for T. casseabriae from Yang et al. (2018)." pageId="1" pageNumber="80">Table 1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,1792,2071]" lastBlockId="2.[136,1452,158,221]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="81" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">
Shrubs with twigs persistently short-pubescent. Leaves elliptic to oblanceolate, 13.8–17.2 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1137,1161,1794,1817]" pageId="1" pageNumber="80"></emphasis>
<quantity box="[1166,1293,1792,1819]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.8" metricValueMax="6.8" metricValueMin="4.8" pageId="1" pageNumber="80" unit="cm" value="5.8" valueMax="6.8" valueMin="4.8">4.8–6.8 cm</quantity>
, base cuneate, apex sharply acuminate, the acumen 
<quantity box="[542,647,1828,1855]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="80" unit="mm" value="10.5" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="5.0">5–16 mm</quantity>
long, glabrous except for hairs along midrib above and below, secondary veins eucamptodromous, 7–10 per side, arcuate; petiole 5.5–9.0 mm long. Inflorescences internodal, 1–2-flowered, peduncles 1.5–3.0 mm long, pedicels ca. 
<quantity box="[604,691,1900,1927]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="80" unit="mm" value="1.2">1.2 mm</quantity>
long, bearing 1 minute bract; buds with petals separated and erect early in development, exceeded by androecium. Flowers bisexual or staminate. Sepals semicircular, ca. 
<quantity box="[1320,1386,1936,1963]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="80" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
long, obtuse, sericeous. Petals white, recurved at anthesis, glabrate on both surfaces, outer petals ovate, ca. 3 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1324,1348,1974,1997]" pageId="1" pageNumber="80"></emphasis>
<quantity box="[1357,1447,1972,1999]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="1" pageNumber="80" unit="mm" value="2.7">2.7 mm</quantity>
, acute, inner petals oblong, ca. 3.0 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[527,551,2010,2033]" pageId="1" pageNumber="80"></emphasis>
2.0 mm, rounded. Stamens 50–100, forming a globose boss ca. 3.0 mm [fluidpreserved] in diameter, clavate, ca. 
<quantity box="[547,636,2044,2071]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="1" pageNumber="80" unit="mm" value="1.7">1.7 mm</quantity>
long, anther connective apex truncate, glabrous to sparsely pubescent. Carpels 4–7, ovaries not examined, stigmas exceeding the tops of the stamens, irregular, pubescent. Receptacle not visible. Fruit of ca. 9 monocarps borne on a short pedicel. Monocarps red in vivo, oblong, acute at the apex.
</paragraph>
