</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,157,688]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,468,337,364]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Conservation status:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chaowasku &amp; D. M. Johnson" authorityYear="2021" box="[468,691,338,364]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Trivalvaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="recurva">
<emphasis box="[468,691,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Trivalvaria recurva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs within the boundaries of a national park, an area not yet widely surveyed for the species. At present, the status of the species should be considered data deficient.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,157,688]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,294,410,436]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Notes:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chaowasku &amp; D. M. Johnson" authorityYear="2021" box="[294,515,410,436]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Trivalvaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="recurva">
<emphasis box="[294,515,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Trivalvaria recurva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinctive among Thai species in having short petals that are separated at the tips from an early stage of development and recurved at anthesis. A photograph of the fruit (
<figureCitation box="[1169,1252,446,472]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1645,1667]" captionTargetBox="[172,1416,815,1617]" captionTargetId="figure-289@4.[170,1416,814,1620]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Photographs of new Trivalvaria species. A. Flower of Trivalvaria stenopetala, Phangnga Province, Thailand. B. Flower of Trivalvaria ochroleuca, Tak Province, Thailand. C. Flower of Trivalvaria recurva, Kanchanaburi Province, Thailand. D. Fruit of Trivalvaria stenopetala, Phangnga Province, Thailand. E. Fruit of probable Trivalvaria ochroleuca from Prachuap Khiri Khan Province, Thailand. F. Fruit of Trivalvaria recurva from Kanchanaburi Province, Thailand.A and D by Simon Gardner from Gardner et al. ST 1944, B by Tanawat Chaowasku, C and F by Piya Chalermglin, E by Thammanoon Temchai." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5757635" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5757635/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Fig. 2F</figureCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Chalermglin, P." pageId="3" pageNumber="82" refId="ref4915" refString="Chalermglin, P. (2001) Family Annonaceae. Ban and Suan, Bangkok. [In Thai]" type="book" year="2001">Chalermglin (2001: 131)</bibRefCitation>
under 
<taxonomicName authority="Blume (1830: 68))" authorityName="Blume" authorityPageNumber="68" authorityYear="1830" box="[343,672,482,509]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Polyalthia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[343,460,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Polyalthia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Blume, C. L." box="[465,672,482,509]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" pagination="1 - 108" refId="ref4885" refString="Blume, C. L. (1830) Flora Javae, volume 2: Anonaceae. Frank, Brussels, pp. 1 - 108 + 53 plates." type="book chapter" year="1830">Blume (1830: 68))</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
shows that the monocarps are red when mature, nearly sessile, oblong and slightly acute at the apex. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chaowasku &amp; D. M. Johnson" authorityYear="2021" box="[479,698,518,544]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Trivalvaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="recurva">
<emphasis box="[479,698,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Trivalvaria recurva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected from an area of 
<collectingRegion box="[1046,1311,518,544]" country="Thailand" name="Kanchanaburi" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Kanchanaburi Province</collectingRegion>
where other narrowly distributed 
<taxonomicName box="[374,512,554,580]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Annonaceae</taxonomicName>
species occur, for example 
<taxonomicName authority="(Saunders, Su &amp; Chalermglin, 2004: 42) Y. C. F. Su &amp; R. M. K. Saunders" authorityName="Y. C. F. Su &amp; R. M. K. Saunders" baseAuthorityName="Saunders, Su &amp; Chalermglin" baseAuthorityPageNumber="42" baseAuthorityYear="2004" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Pseuduvaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="phuyensis">
<emphasis box="[835,1096,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Pseuduvaria phuyensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Saunders, R. M. K. &amp; Su, Y. C. F. &amp; Chalermglin, P." pageId="3" pageNumber="82" pagination="42 - 49" refId="ref5442" refString="Saunders, R. M. K., Su, Y. C. F. &amp; Chalermglin, P. (2004) Craibella phuyensis (Annonaceae): a new genus and species from Thailand. Systematic Botany 29: 42 - 49. https: // doi. org / 10.1600 / 036364404772974202" type="journal article" year="2004">Saunders, Su &amp; Chalermglin, 2004: 42</bibRefCitation>
) Y.C.F.Su &amp; R.M.K.Saunders
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Su, Y. C. F. &amp; Chaowasku, T. &amp; Saunders, R. M. K." box="[620,848,590,616]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" pagination="30 - 39" refId="ref5586" refString="Su, Y. C. F., Chaowasku, T. &amp; Saunders, R. M. K. (2010) An extended phylogeny of Pseuduvaria (Annonaceae) with descriptions of three new species and a reassessment of the generic status of Oreomitra. Systematic Botany 35: 30 - 39. https: // doi. org / 10.1600 / 036364410790862533" type="journal article" year="2010">
Su 
<emphasis box="[658,717,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">et al.</emphasis>
(2010: 37)
</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chaowasku &amp; D. M. Johnson" authorityYear="2021" box="[861,1121,590,616]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Trivalvaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ochroleuca">
<emphasis box="[861,1121,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Trivalvaria ochroleuca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only other 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Trivalvaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1325,1451,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Trivalvaria</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
known from this area and can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chaowasku &amp; D. M. Johnson" authorityYear="2021" box="[814,928,627,652]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Trivalvaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="recurva">
<emphasis box="[814,928,627,652]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">T. recurva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its shorter blunt leaf acumen 
<quantity box="[1295,1388,626,652]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" unit="mm" value="5.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="3.0">3–8 mm</quantity>
long, inflorescences sub-opposite the leaves and greater numbers of stamens and carpels.
</paragraph>
